Upgrade procedure for ldns

Source: https://nlnetlabs.nl/downloads/ldns/ldns-VERSION.tar.gz

To upgrade to a new version:

1. Download and extract the release tarball (NOT a git checkout -- the
   tarball ships generated files such as configure that the git repo
   does not).
2. Use the vendor-update skill (vendor branch vendor/ldns/dist,
   in-tree prefix contrib/ldns).
3. Regenerate the in-tree generated headers and refresh local patches
   after the subtree merge (see below).

Vendor branch vs. in-tree copy:
  - The vendor branch (vendor/ldns/dist) holds the FULL upstream tarball
    at the repo root, including doc/, contrib/ and examples/.
  - The in-tree copy (contrib/ldns) excludes doc/, contrib/ (Perl/Python
    bindings) and examples/. They are dropped during the subtree merge by
    resolving the modify/delete conflicts as keep-deleted:
        git rm -rf contrib/ldns/doc contrib/ldns/contrib contrib/ldns/examples

Generated headers (NOT shipped by upstream; produced by ./configure):
  - ldns/config.h, ldns/util.h, ldns/common.h, ldns/net.h are generated
    from the corresponding *.in templates.
  - ldns/internal.h is a MidnightBSD/FreeBSD-added header (no .in, not in
    the tarball); carry it forward.
  - Do NOT run ./configure to regenerate these on a non-MidnightBSD host
    (e.g. a Linux build host) -- it would bake host-specific values into
    config.h/common.h/net.h. Instead regenerate by delta: diff the old vs
    new *.in templates and apply only the real changes to the existing
    in-tree headers. Always bump LDNS_VERSION/LDNS_REVISION in util.h and
    PACKAGE_STRING/PACKAGE_VERSION in config.h to the new version.

Local patches applied on top of upstream (all are -Wmissing-prototypes
fixes for the WARNS=3 in-tree build, which compiles the sources directly
via lib/libldns/Makefile rather than the upstream build system):
  - Add ldns/internal.h and "#include <ldns/internal.h>" to the .c files
    that define/use the shared internal helpers (host2str.c, packet.c,
    rr.c, str2host.c, dnssec_sign.c, dnssec_zone.c, zone.c). Where the
    upstream file carries its own inline forward declaration of one of
    these helpers, it is removed in favor of the internal.h prototype.
  - util.c: inline prototype for ldns_serial_arithmitics_gmtime_r().
  - ldns/parse.h: prototype for ldns_fget_token_l_resolv_conf().
  These auto-merge cleanly across minor upstream releases; the build with
  WARNS=3 is the gate -- a missing-prototype error means internal.h needs
  a new entry, a duplicate/conflicting one means upstream now declares it
  itself and the local copy should be dropped.

Build check:
    cd lib/libldns && make          # WARNS=3, must be clean
    cd usr.bin/drill && make
    cd usr.bin/host  && make         # uses contrib/ldns-host, links libldns
  (usr.sbin/unbound/* also link libprivateldns.)

Notes:
  - The libtool soname (VERSION_INFO) is irrelevant in-tree: libldns is
    built PRIVATELIB, so the upstream .so version bump does not matter.
  - lib/libldns/Makefile uses an explicit SRCS list; if a future release
    adds or removes a top-level *.c source, update SRCS accordingly. The
    1.8.4 -> 1.9.2 update did not change the source set.
  - Last imported: 1.9.2 (2026-06-27). 1.9.1 fixed CVE-2026-10846
    (off-path response spoofing: ldns now matches the response source
    address/port, transaction ID and question against the query).
